gov.anl.ipns.ViewTools.Components
Interface IPointList3D

All Superinterfaces:
IVirtualArray
All Known Subinterfaces:
IPhysicalArray3D, IPhysicalArray3DList, ISparseArray3D, ISparseArray3DList
All Known Implementing Classes:
PhysicalArray3D, PhysicalArray3DList, PointList3D, SparseArray3D, SparseArray3DList
public interface IPointList3D
extends IVirtualArray

This interface is intended for classes that must store scattered three dimensional points. The size of a Array must be given by the constructor, but the values may be set later. For each point in the array, there is an associated integer index. The range of the index runs from zero to the total number of points the array can hold. If no positions are given at construction, the points are intitalized as Vector3D objects with Float.NaN for the x, y, and z fields.

set

void set(int index_start,
         int index_end,
         Vector3D[] points)
Sets 3d points for each index in range, including the start and end indices. The first value in the points array is the starting value to be set at index_start. Points should have at least a point for each index in given range. Any points beyond this size are ignored.

Parameters:
index_start - First index of the range.
index_end - Last index of the range.
points - The 3d coordinates.
Throws:
java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If index is outside of valid range of indices: 0...getNumPoints().
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If given points array is smaller than specified range.
